WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.472 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.472 --> 00:00:18.370 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.370 --> 00:00:20.450 align:middle line:84%
Cynthia James was
on the fast track

00:00:20.450 --> 00:00:23.630 align:middle line:84%
as an actress, singer, and
wife of a high profile actor.

00:00:23.630 --> 00:00:26.470 align:middle line:84%
But what no one but her
closest friends and family knew

00:00:26.470 --> 00:00:29.260 align:middle line:84%
was that she suffered
horribly from emotional trauma

00:00:29.260 --> 00:00:31.190 align:middle line:90%
and a lack of self-confidence.

00:00:31.190 --> 00:00:33.830 align:middle line:84%
While this is not an
uncommon story in itself

00:00:33.830 --> 00:00:36.370 align:middle line:84%
the twist comes when
Cynthia took responsibility

00:00:36.370 --> 00:00:39.030 align:middle line:90%
for her healing as a warrior.

00:00:39.030 --> 00:00:41.830 align:middle line:84%
Her journey of healing
resulted in becoming

00:00:41.830 --> 00:00:43.840 align:middle line:84%
an inspirational
author and lecturer

00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:47.340 align:middle line:84%
who has the grace and presence
to take this message deep.

00:00:47.340 --> 00:00:50.140 align:middle line:84%
She joins us today to speak
about how we can reveal

00:00:50.140 --> 00:00:51.720 align:middle line:90%
the very best of ourselves.

00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:54.020 align:middle line:84%
And Cynthia, it's
wonderful to see you again.

00:00:54.020 --> 00:00:55.910 align:middle line:84%
It's wonderful to see you
and to be with you again.

00:00:55.910 --> 00:00:58.150 align:middle line:84%
And to have moments to connect.
-Yes.

00:00:58.150 --> 00:00:59.700 align:middle line:84%
And we had a little
bit of time off camera.

00:00:59.700 --> 00:01:01.640 align:middle line:84%
And last time I saw
you was in Sedona.

00:01:01.640 --> 00:01:04.690 align:middle line:84%
And we had a
magnificent conversation

00:01:04.690 --> 00:01:07.620 align:middle line:84%
about the previous book
that you had written to what

00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:09.600 align:middle line:90%
you're working on right now.

00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:12.800 align:middle line:84%
And I really wanted to go
back into that conversation

00:01:12.800 --> 00:01:18.440 align:middle line:84%
because it's a very personal
and sometimes painful story.

00:01:18.440 --> 00:01:20.730 align:middle line:84%
But it gives other
people who have been

00:01:20.730 --> 00:01:23.000 align:middle line:84%
through these
experiences something

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:26.520 align:middle line:84%
that they can really kind
of hold on to and relate to.

00:01:26.520 --> 00:01:30.190 align:middle line:84%
And I would appreciate it if you
would start by kind of giving

00:01:30.190 --> 00:01:31.950 align:middle line:84%
us a little of the
background of your life

00:01:31.950 --> 00:01:35.660 align:middle line:84%
as the world saw it, which
was very big and very shiny.

00:01:35.660 --> 00:01:37.100 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about
what your life was

00:01:37.100 --> 00:01:40.130 align:middle line:84%
like before we go into what was
going on underneath that story.

00:01:40.130 --> 00:01:40.830 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:01:40.830 --> 00:01:45.010 align:middle line:10%
Well I was married
to a famous actor.

00:01:45.010 --> 00:01:47.140 align:middle line:10%
We had a beautiful
home in Malibu.

00:01:47.140 --> 00:01:49.300 align:middle line:10%
Our children went
to the best schools.

00:01:49.300 --> 00:01:51.450 align:middle line:10%
We traveled all over the world.

00:01:51.450 --> 00:01:54.420 align:middle line:10%
It was really incredible.

00:01:54.420 --> 00:01:56.760 align:middle line:84%
I was making my living
as an actress as well.

00:01:56.760 --> 00:01:59.010 align:middle line:84%
And so you know, I was
living the dream life.

00:01:59.010 --> 00:02:01.581 align:middle line:84%
Talk about your life as
an actress a little bit.

00:02:01.581 --> 00:02:02.280 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:02:02.280 --> 00:02:05.080 align:middle line:84%
I was the original Lexie
on Days of our Lives.

00:02:05.080 --> 00:02:08.280 align:middle line:84%
And so it was great
because I love theater.

00:02:08.280 --> 00:02:10.860 align:middle line:84%
And you know soap operas
really are theater.

00:02:10.860 --> 00:02:14.950 align:middle line:84%
You're doing everything kind of
live, and quick, and wonderful.

00:02:14.950 --> 00:02:16.350 align:middle line:90%
And so that was great.

00:02:16.350 --> 00:02:18.530 align:middle line:84%
I'd go home, I'd
be with the family.

00:02:18.530 --> 00:02:24.240 align:middle line:84%
And so I felt on a
certain level as though I

00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:27.910 align:middle line:84%
had moved out of my
history and created

00:02:27.910 --> 00:02:29.340 align:middle line:90%
this extraordinary life.

00:02:29.340 --> 00:02:34.360 align:middle line:84%
And so it was surprising
to me that these things

00:02:34.360 --> 00:02:35.480 align:middle line:90%
kept coming up.

00:02:35.480 --> 00:02:38.940 align:middle line:84%
These feelings, and these
emotions, and these behaviors

00:02:38.940 --> 00:02:42.870 align:middle line:84%
kept coming up in
unexpected ways.

00:02:42.870 --> 00:02:45.860 align:middle line:84%
And you try to manage them/
you try to push them down.

00:02:45.860 --> 00:02:47.410 align:middle line:90%
You try to deal with them.

00:02:47.410 --> 00:02:51.190 align:middle line:84%
But I became aware that it
was time for me to really look

00:02:51.190 --> 00:02:57.900 align:middle line:84%
at them because I couldn't mask
what was happening any longer.

00:02:57.900 --> 00:02:58.840 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:02:58.840 --> 00:03:01.080 align:middle line:84%
And you know it's
interesting because we

00:03:01.080 --> 00:03:02.570 align:middle line:84%
often hear this
story about people

00:03:02.570 --> 00:03:04.740 align:middle line:90%
who are living "the big life."

00:03:04.740 --> 00:03:07.360 align:middle line:84%
And oftentimes we read
about them in the headlines

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:10.640 align:middle line:84%
because they end up
in either arrest--

00:03:10.640 --> 00:03:13.620 align:middle line:84%
developing an arrest record
or in rehab or something.

00:03:13.620 --> 00:03:17.000 align:middle line:84%
But with you, you
had the presence

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:19.590 align:middle line:84%
and you had the
courage to begin diving

00:03:19.590 --> 00:03:21.800 align:middle line:90%
into the deep end of that well.

00:03:21.800 --> 00:03:24.750 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk about
how deep that well went.

00:03:24.750 --> 00:03:29.570 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm speaking about
coming from a lineage of women

00:03:29.570 --> 00:03:33.720 align:middle line:84%
that goes back at least
five generations of abuse.

00:03:33.720 --> 00:03:36.950 align:middle line:84%
And so let's begin
at whatever you

00:03:36.950 --> 00:03:40.080 align:middle line:84%
feel is the appropriate
point in that story.

00:03:40.080 --> 00:03:43.390 align:middle line:84%
And certainly going back to
your grandmother at least.

00:03:43.390 --> 00:03:46.380 align:middle line:84%
So we can see and think
of it in our own light

00:03:46.380 --> 00:03:50.290 align:middle line:84%
how these things-- how
these patterns reoccur.

00:03:50.290 --> 00:03:52.660 align:middle line:84%
You know I'd love
to talk about this.

00:03:52.660 --> 00:03:55.160 align:middle line:90%
My grandmother was born in 1898.

00:03:55.160 --> 00:03:59.570 align:middle line:84%
Her name was Mary Swain,
and she died at 99.

00:03:59.570 --> 00:04:03.630 align:middle line:84%
She raised four children
in Alabama on a farm.

00:04:03.630 --> 00:04:06.580 align:middle line:84%
At a time when--
and she was alone--

00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:08.960 align:middle line:84%
and it was a time when
black people in this country

00:04:08.960 --> 00:04:10.025 align:middle line:90%
were really challenged.

00:04:10.025 --> 00:04:12.480 align:middle line:84%
You know In the way in which
she took care of her children

00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:15.640 align:middle line:84%
was taking her clothes--
going to pick up

00:04:15.640 --> 00:04:18.050 align:middle line:84%
the clothes of the Caucasians
in the neighborhood,

00:04:18.050 --> 00:04:19.899 align:middle line:84%
and taking it back
home and washing it,

00:04:19.899 --> 00:04:23.150 align:middle line:84%
and having her kids help
iron, and then take them back.

00:04:23.150 --> 00:04:25.480 align:middle line:84%
So that she could take
care of her children,

00:04:25.480 --> 00:04:27.460 align:middle line:90%
that they could get educated.

00:04:27.460 --> 00:04:30.570 align:middle line:84%
And then she moved to
Minnesota, bought a home,

00:04:30.570 --> 00:04:36.960 align:middle line:84%
and created this life for the
family that was possibilities.

00:04:36.960 --> 00:04:38.730 align:middle line:84%
The challenge with
all of that though

00:04:38.730 --> 00:04:41.510 align:middle line:84%
is that while the
children-- my grandfather

00:04:41.510 --> 00:04:45.110 align:middle line:84%
was there before he left--
there was a great deal of abuse.

00:04:45.110 --> 00:04:49.400 align:middle line:84%
And my mother, who was
incredibly beautiful.

00:04:49.400 --> 00:04:51.200 align:middle line:84%
I mean she was like--
-Like you,

00:04:51.200 --> 00:04:53.420 align:middle line:90%
Oh thank you.

00:04:53.420 --> 00:04:55.970 align:middle line:84%
I mean she was like a Rita
Hayworth she was so amazing.

00:04:55.970 --> 00:05:00.480 align:middle line:90%
And intelligent and skilled.

00:05:00.480 --> 00:05:04.490 align:middle line:84%
But my grandfather treated
her terribly because she

00:05:04.490 --> 00:05:06.030 align:middle line:90%
was very intuitive as well.

00:05:06.030 --> 00:05:09.760 align:middle line:84%
And so there were experiences
I think that were mystical.

00:05:09.760 --> 00:05:11.790 align:middle line:84%
And he didn't want
her to have those.

00:05:11.790 --> 00:05:14.100 align:middle line:84%
And so he would lock her
in under the house in

00:05:14.100 --> 00:05:15.490 align:middle line:90%
those hot boxes that they had.

00:05:15.490 --> 00:05:17.260 align:middle line:90%
Lock her under?

00:05:17.260 --> 00:05:18.490 align:middle line:90%
How do you even do that?

00:05:18.490 --> 00:05:20.250 align:middle line:84%
How do you get
someone in the box?

00:05:20.250 --> 00:05:22.010 align:middle line:90%
Well you squeeze them in.

00:05:22.010 --> 00:05:25.600 align:middle line:84%
And so she was always
paranoid and always

00:05:25.600 --> 00:05:26.720 align:middle line:90%
feeling disconnected.

00:05:26.720 --> 00:05:31.080 align:middle line:84%
And when I started uncovering
all of this in my family

00:05:31.080 --> 00:05:34.620 align:middle line:84%
and started to recognize
what was going on with me

00:05:34.620 --> 00:05:36.010 align:middle line:90%
I did research.

00:05:36.010 --> 00:05:37.610 align:middle line:84%
I went to the University
of Santa Monica

00:05:37.610 --> 00:05:38.930 align:middle line:90%
and we had to do a genogram.

00:05:38.930 --> 00:05:41.640 align:middle line:84%
Five generations of
women had been abused,

00:05:41.640 --> 00:05:43.750 align:middle line:90%
raped, traumatized.

00:05:43.750 --> 00:05:46.450 align:middle line:84%
Did that happen to-- was
it your great grandmother?

00:05:46.450 --> 00:05:48.740 align:middle line:84%
It was my great
grandmother who was a slave,

00:05:48.740 --> 00:05:49.890 align:middle line:90%
brought over as a slave.

00:05:49.890 --> 00:05:51.870 align:middle line:84%
And the slave owner
raped her in front

00:05:51.870 --> 00:05:54.780 align:middle line:90%
of the entire slave group.

00:05:54.780 --> 00:05:56.840 align:middle line:90%
And she conceived.

00:05:56.840 --> 00:05:59.150 align:middle line:90%
And so she hated her child.

00:05:59.150 --> 00:06:01.910 align:middle line:84%
And so that continued the
abuse on another level.

00:06:01.910 --> 00:06:07.590 align:middle line:84%
And so it was very-- it was
very disheartening on one level

00:06:07.590 --> 00:06:10.510 align:middle line:84%
to find out that it had
been going on for so long.

00:06:10.510 --> 00:06:12.630 align:middle line:84%
But there was this kernel
within me that said,

00:06:12.630 --> 00:06:15.400 align:middle line:90%
well maybe I can shift it.

00:06:15.400 --> 00:06:18.570 align:middle line:84%
Because my stepfather
was the perpetrator.

00:06:18.570 --> 00:06:20.920 align:middle line:84%
My mother married for the
second time to get out.

00:06:20.920 --> 00:06:23.230 align:middle line:84%
Because my biological
father left pretty early,

00:06:23.230 --> 00:06:25.320 align:middle line:90%
he was an alcoholic.

00:06:25.320 --> 00:06:29.710 align:middle line:84%
And so she married this man
who beat her consistently.

00:06:29.710 --> 00:06:31.130 align:middle line:90%
Did you witness the beatings?

00:06:31.130 --> 00:06:32.580 align:middle line:90%
Oh, totally.

00:06:32.580 --> 00:06:34.330 align:middle line:84%
-That's very difficult.
-Very.

00:06:34.330 --> 00:06:39.710 align:middle line:84%
I remember being about six years
old and hearing her scream.

00:06:39.710 --> 00:06:42.700 align:middle line:84%
She was pregnant with my
brother and going into the room,

00:06:42.700 --> 00:06:44.880 align:middle line:84%
and he was straddling
her, smacking her.

00:06:44.880 --> 00:06:47.340 align:middle line:90%
And she's screaming get out.

00:06:47.340 --> 00:06:49.370 align:middle line:84%
Because she wanted
me to be safe.

00:06:49.370 --> 00:06:50.587 align:middle line:84%
-Telling you to get out?
-Yeah.

00:06:50.587 --> 00:06:51.320 align:middle line:90%
Telling me to get out.

00:06:51.320 --> 00:06:52.310 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:06:52.310 --> 00:06:56.920 align:middle line:84%
And so I was mouthy
and expressive.

00:06:56.920 --> 00:07:00.670 align:middle line:84%
And so that probably did not
help the relationship with him.

00:07:00.670 --> 00:07:03.450 align:middle line:84%
And this went on-- I
was six years old--

00:07:03.450 --> 00:07:06.230 align:middle line:90%
this went on for almost a year.

00:07:06.230 --> 00:07:09.570 align:middle line:84%
Until at some point
something in her

00:07:09.570 --> 00:07:12.070 align:middle line:90%
said I can't do this anymore.

00:07:12.070 --> 00:07:15.110 align:middle line:84%
And she had my uncle
come and take everything

00:07:15.110 --> 00:07:17.040 align:middle line:90%
that she owned in sheets.

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:20.260 align:middle line:84%
And she got out because she
only had a 20 minute window

00:07:20.260 --> 00:07:24.260 align:middle line:90%
before my stepfather came back.

00:07:24.260 --> 00:07:28.350 align:middle line:84%
And so it was-- I didn't
remember all this until I was

00:07:28.350 --> 00:07:30.190 align:middle line:90%
in my 30s and I was in therapy.

00:07:30.190 --> 00:07:32.840 align:middle line:84%
And I was really
trying to find out

00:07:32.840 --> 00:07:35.370 align:middle line:84%
why I was disconnected
at points and I

00:07:35.370 --> 00:07:37.200 align:middle line:90%
would disassociate at points.

00:07:37.200 --> 00:07:41.850 align:middle line:84%
And so it was really quite
interesting for me to say,

00:07:41.850 --> 00:07:45.890 align:middle line:90%
oh, this is why.

00:07:45.890 --> 00:07:46.680 align:middle line:90%
To open to it.

00:07:46.680 --> 00:07:48.250 align:middle line:84%
There was a therapist
at one point who

00:07:48.250 --> 00:07:51.900 align:middle line:84%
said quite innocently,
have you ever

00:07:51.900 --> 00:07:53.470 align:middle line:90%
been abused by your father?

00:07:53.470 --> 00:07:57.730 align:middle line:84%
At which time I fell out of
the chair on the floor and was

00:07:57.730 --> 00:07:58.980 align:middle line:90%
curled up.

00:07:58.980 --> 00:08:01.720 align:middle line:84%
And that opened up the
door for me to look at it.

00:08:01.720 --> 00:08:06.370 align:middle line:84%
But had you not had memory
of it up to that point?

00:08:06.370 --> 00:08:07.290 align:middle line:90%
You had shut it out.

00:08:07.290 --> 00:08:11.490 align:middle line:84%
You must have compartmentalised
your emotions in mind

00:08:11.490 --> 00:08:14.360 align:middle line:84%
to the extent because
you couldn't bear

00:08:14.360 --> 00:08:16.210 align:middle line:90%
it-- to even think about it.

00:08:16.210 --> 00:08:18.390 align:middle line:84%
You must have just pushed
it to the back of the mind.

00:08:18.390 --> 00:08:19.089 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:08:19.089 --> 00:08:21.750 align:middle line:84%
I think really what happens
is you fight, flight,

00:08:21.750 --> 00:08:24.520 align:middle line:90%
or you leave.

00:08:24.520 --> 00:08:25.690 align:middle line:90%
And I dissociated.

00:08:25.690 --> 00:08:28.850 align:middle line:84%
I think I just pulled
myself out of my body.

00:08:28.850 --> 00:08:31.460 align:middle line:84%
And I remember being
in therapy and there

00:08:31.460 --> 00:08:34.360 align:middle line:84%
was something going
on and the therapist

00:08:34.360 --> 00:08:38.140 align:middle line:90%
said to me, where are you?

00:08:38.140 --> 00:08:39.950 align:middle line:84%
And I was aware
that a part of me

00:08:39.950 --> 00:08:42.909 align:middle line:84%
was kind of hanging up
on the ceiling watching,

00:08:42.909 --> 00:08:44.960 align:middle line:90%
that I had left my body.

00:08:44.960 --> 00:08:48.280 align:middle line:84%
And so part of the work was
to get me back into my body

00:08:48.280 --> 00:08:50.049 align:middle line:84%
so I could feel.
-Oh.

00:08:50.049 --> 00:08:56.020 align:middle line:84%
So now during these
experiences that you endured

00:08:56.020 --> 00:08:58.560 align:middle line:84%
with your stepfather
were you out of body

00:08:58.560 --> 00:09:00.420 align:middle line:90%
during those experiences?

00:09:00.420 --> 00:09:01.260 align:middle line:90%
I must have been.

00:09:01.260 --> 00:09:03.410 align:middle line:84%
I had-- there were little
memories that came back.

00:09:03.410 --> 00:09:05.380 align:middle line:84%
And I was so grateful
my mother was alive.

00:09:05.380 --> 00:09:08.920 align:middle line:84%
Because you know the remembering
of those kinds of things,

00:09:08.920 --> 00:09:11.240 align:middle line:84%
there's a lot of controversy
about whether it happened

00:09:11.240 --> 00:09:13.790 align:middle line:84%
and whether the therapist
implanted stuff.

00:09:13.790 --> 00:09:15.490 align:middle line:84%
But when I went
back to my mother

00:09:15.490 --> 00:09:17.840 align:middle line:84%
and I started describing
these memories

00:09:17.840 --> 00:09:20.830 align:middle line:84%
and these little flashes
she began to weep.

00:09:20.830 --> 00:09:23.340 align:middle line:84%
Because she thought
I wouldn't remember

00:09:23.340 --> 00:09:25.010 align:middle line:84%
because I was so young.
-Oh.

00:09:25.010 --> 00:09:25.780 align:middle line:90%
How old were you?

00:09:25.780 --> 00:09:26.550 align:middle line:90%
I was six.

00:09:26.550 --> 00:09:28.180 align:middle line:90%
You were six.

00:09:28.180 --> 00:09:31.050 align:middle line:84%
And so we're talking pretty
extreme abuse I take it?

00:09:31.050 --> 00:09:31.750 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:09:31.750 --> 00:09:32.580 align:middle line:90%
It was pretty extreme.

00:09:32.580 --> 00:09:33.710 align:middle line:90%
Pretty extreme.

00:09:33.710 --> 00:09:36.260 align:middle line:84%
And so as you're working
with this therapist and this

00:09:36.260 --> 00:09:39.680 align:middle line:84%
is being revealed from
you to your conscious mind

00:09:39.680 --> 00:09:41.440 align:middle line:90%
for its understanding.

00:09:41.440 --> 00:09:45.360 align:middle line:84%
What was your very-- you say
you were in a fetal position

00:09:45.360 --> 00:09:48.100 align:middle line:84%
on the floor-- what was
your first response?

00:09:48.100 --> 00:09:50.120 align:middle line:84%
Because we want to talk
about the lineage of what

00:09:50.120 --> 00:09:52.840 align:middle line:84%
happens once you're
confronted with this

00:09:52.840 --> 00:09:54.610 align:middle line:84%
if it has been
erased essentially

00:09:54.610 --> 00:09:56.960 align:middle line:90%
from your conscious awareness.

00:09:56.960 --> 00:10:00.700 align:middle line:84%
You know I remember
the therapist getting

00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:04.090 align:middle line:84%
on the floor with me and
basically kind of holding me

00:10:04.090 --> 00:10:06.530 align:middle line:90%
and telling me I was safe.

00:10:06.530 --> 00:10:08.190 align:middle line:90%
