00:19:49.050 --> 00:19:52.370 align:middle line:84%
I mean through art
up to real life

00:19:52.370 --> 00:19:54.460 align:middle line:84%
That's the very thing that is
the beginning of the healing,

00:19:54.460 --> 00:19:55.690 align:middle line:84%
isn't it?
-Well, totally.

00:19:55.690 --> 00:20:00.000 align:middle line:84%
Because really in the depths
of the pain is the healing.

00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:02.450 align:middle line:84%
And I really think that all
of these things that we go

00:20:02.450 --> 00:20:04.660 align:middle line:84%
through, and all these
experiences and the awakenings

00:20:04.660 --> 00:20:07.330 align:middle line:84%
that we have, are to bring
us to a point of healing

00:20:07.330 --> 00:20:08.920 align:middle line:90%
and the health and wellness.

00:20:08.920 --> 00:20:15.590 align:middle line:84%
But but being vulnerable like
that is really-- if you don't

00:20:15.590 --> 00:20:17.310 align:middle line:84%
know what to do with
the vulnerability,

00:20:17.310 --> 00:20:20.050 align:middle line:84%
and if you don't think that
there is safety in the world,

00:20:20.050 --> 00:20:23.310 align:middle line:84%
then you want to cover it
up as soon as possible.

00:20:23.310 --> 00:20:26.270 align:middle line:84%
Because you're
terrified that that pain

00:20:26.270 --> 00:20:29.051 align:middle line:84%
will come back in a way that's
unexpected and brutal maybe.

00:20:29.051 --> 00:20:30.970 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
And that maybe you can't manage.

00:20:30.970 --> 00:20:33.370 align:middle line:84%
You've learned how to
manage it and contain it up

00:20:33.370 --> 00:20:34.170 align:middle line:90%
to that point.

00:20:34.170 --> 00:20:37.400 align:middle line:84%
There was a woman who
ultimately came into your life

00:20:37.400 --> 00:20:41.031 align:middle line:84%
and was really able to
help you open up to this

00:20:41.031 --> 00:20:41.730 align:middle line:90%
and move through.

00:20:41.730 --> 00:20:43.570 align:middle line:84%
Can you talk a little bit
about that experience?

00:20:43.570 --> 00:20:45.900 align:middle line:84%
There was a woman
who-- who said,

00:20:45.900 --> 00:20:48.440 align:middle line:84%
you do not have
to live this way.

00:20:48.440 --> 00:20:50.229 align:middle line:84%
-That's the lady.
-Yeah.

00:20:50.229 --> 00:20:51.900 align:middle line:90%
You don't have to live this way.

00:20:51.900 --> 00:20:54.040 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
sell yourself out.

00:20:54.040 --> 00:20:56.700 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to give
yourself away to be loved.

00:20:56.700 --> 00:20:57.850 align:middle line:84%
But for some
reason you actually

00:20:57.850 --> 00:20:59.151 align:middle line:90%
heard the message that time.

00:20:59.151 --> 00:21:00.650 align:middle line:84%
It's can't be the first
time you've heard it.

00:21:00.650 --> 00:21:02.450 align:middle line:90%
Well, because she loved me.

00:21:02.450 --> 00:21:03.260 align:middle line:90%
I see.

00:21:03.260 --> 00:21:06.640 align:middle line:84%
She loved me and didn't
want anything from me.

00:21:06.640 --> 00:21:11.230 align:middle line:84%
Wasn't trying to mold
me or control me.

00:21:11.230 --> 00:21:13.270 align:middle line:90%
She just wanted me to wake up.

00:21:13.270 --> 00:21:16.430 align:middle line:84%
And it was with
such love and heart.

00:21:16.430 --> 00:21:18.010 align:middle line:84%
And this is a thing
we've witnessed

00:21:18.010 --> 00:21:20.160 align:middle line:84%
in so many other people's
lives, all of us have.

00:21:20.160 --> 00:21:24.060 align:middle line:84%
Where we've seen someone who's
really struggling in life.

00:21:24.060 --> 00:21:26.290 align:middle line:90%
Who is sabotaging their lives.

00:21:26.290 --> 00:21:28.260 align:middle line:84%
Who's putting up
with things they

00:21:28.260 --> 00:21:30.450 align:middle line:90%
should not be putting up with.

00:21:30.450 --> 00:21:33.150 align:middle line:90%
And you can't help them.

00:21:33.150 --> 00:21:36.175 align:middle line:84%
You can-- another person
may have said that to you.

00:21:36.175 --> 00:21:38.980 align:middle line:84%
You may have had people saying
it to you every other week.

00:21:38.980 --> 00:21:43.000 align:middle line:84%
But until something in you
could trust that that was true,

00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:45.580 align:middle line:84%
and you were ready to hear
the message, we can't hear it.

00:21:45.580 --> 00:21:46.620 align:middle line:90%
That's the frustrating part.

00:21:46.620 --> 00:21:48.720 align:middle line:84%
We want to go around fixing--
trying to fix ourselves.

00:21:48.720 --> 00:21:51.390 align:middle line:84%
We're going around try to
fix each other all the time.

00:21:51.390 --> 00:21:53.680 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you just did this-- and
giving her a big fat opinion.

00:21:53.680 --> 00:21:57.331 align:middle line:84%
But the reality is you
can't tell anybody else.

00:21:57.331 --> 00:21:59.180 align:middle line:84%
-No.
-Until it's time.

00:21:59.180 --> 00:22:00.860 align:middle line:84%
You can't do anything.
-Nope.

00:22:00.860 --> 00:22:02.430 align:middle line:90%
You can't do anything.

00:22:02.430 --> 00:22:04.740 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is is
that I do believe

00:22:04.740 --> 00:22:07.730 align:middle line:84%
that sometimes those people
telling us those things

00:22:07.730 --> 00:22:09.020 align:middle line:90%
plant seeds within us.

00:22:09.020 --> 00:22:12.370 align:middle line:84%
And then somebody shows up
and puts the right water on it

00:22:12.370 --> 00:22:13.940 align:middle line:90%
and it blossoms.

00:22:13.940 --> 00:22:17.330 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is is
that when you look

00:22:17.330 --> 00:22:20.170 align:middle line:84%
at any kind of addiction, any
kind of challenges in people's

00:22:20.170 --> 00:22:24.780 align:middle line:84%
lives, until they
want to change nothing

00:22:24.780 --> 00:22:26.470 align:middle line:90%
is going to make them change.

00:22:26.470 --> 00:22:30.390 align:middle line:84%
You know I went to Al Anon
because of my father's

00:22:30.390 --> 00:22:31.460 align:middle line:90%
alcoholism and stuff.

00:22:31.460 --> 00:22:34.280 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, you
can't hide the alcohol.

00:22:34.280 --> 00:22:35.850 align:middle line:90%
You can't talk him out of it.

00:22:35.850 --> 00:22:37.870 align:middle line:84%
You can't manipulate
them out of it.

00:22:37.870 --> 00:22:40.941 align:middle line:84%
Until they want to change
they're going to just do

00:22:40.941 --> 00:22:41.640 align:middle line:90%
what they need to do.

00:22:41.640 --> 00:22:43.920 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's true
for every human being.

00:22:43.920 --> 00:22:44.920 align:middle line:90%
I agree.

00:22:44.920 --> 00:22:45.630 align:middle line:90%
I agree.

00:22:45.630 --> 00:22:47.510 align:middle line:84%
And that's probably the
most frustrating thing

00:22:47.510 --> 00:22:49.840 align:middle line:84%
of our personal
relationships with others.

00:22:49.840 --> 00:22:51.150 align:middle line:84%
Especially if you're
the kind of person

00:22:51.150 --> 00:22:54.480 align:middle line:84%
that really wants to be of
some kind or service or help.

00:22:54.480 --> 00:22:56.880 align:middle line:84%
It's not your business
until that person's ready.

00:22:56.880 --> 00:22:57.580 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:22:57.580 --> 00:22:59.060 align:middle line:84%
Because you can only
change yourself.

00:22:59.060 --> 00:22:59.770 align:middle line:84%
Right.
Exactly.

00:22:59.770 --> 00:23:01.070 align:middle line:90%
You can only heal yourself.

00:23:01.070 --> 00:23:04.060 align:middle line:84%
And I think sometimes people
try to change other people

00:23:04.060 --> 00:23:07.800 align:middle line:84%
because they are afraid if
they change they're going

00:23:07.800 --> 00:23:09.860 align:middle line:90%
to-- the relationship will end.

00:23:09.860 --> 00:23:11.690 align:middle line:84%
-It did for you.
-Oh.

00:23:11.690 --> 00:23:13.680 align:middle line:84%
It totally did.
It totally did.

00:23:13.680 --> 00:23:15.830 align:middle line:84%
So tell us what happened
when you started changing.

00:23:15.830 --> 00:23:19.681 align:middle line:84%
I mean you're talking
about losses in friendship.

00:23:19.681 --> 00:23:20.380 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:23:20.380 --> 00:23:23.030 align:middle line:84%
A real breakage because you're
becoming and emerging-- you're

00:23:23.030 --> 00:23:25.021 align:middle line:84%
emerging into a
different human being.

00:23:25.021 --> 00:23:25.720 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:23:25.720 --> 00:23:28.560 align:middle line:84%
My spirituality became
very important to me.

00:23:28.560 --> 00:23:34.600 align:middle line:84%
My spiritual practice, my work
with the therapist, my wanting

00:23:34.600 --> 00:23:37.000 align:middle line:84%
desperately to get
clear about who I was

00:23:37.000 --> 00:23:38.920 align:middle line:90%
and what was going on with me.

00:23:38.920 --> 00:23:40.750 align:middle line:90%
And it changed the dance.

00:23:40.750 --> 00:23:43.190 align:middle line:84%
It changed the dance
in the relationship.

00:23:43.190 --> 00:23:46.070 align:middle line:84%
And he was having
his own challenges.

00:23:46.070 --> 00:23:48.580 align:middle line:90%
And so they escalated.

00:23:48.580 --> 00:23:51.240 align:middle line:84%
And because I was
becoming clear,

00:23:51.240 --> 00:23:54.890 align:middle line:84%
and because I wouldn't go
back into that old behavior,

00:23:54.890 --> 00:23:57.030 align:middle line:84%
he didn't know
what to do with it.

00:23:57.030 --> 00:24:01.780 align:middle line:84%
And so ultimately he opted
out of the relationship.

00:24:01.780 --> 00:24:04.550 align:middle line:84%
And it was challenging
for me and the kids.

00:24:04.550 --> 00:24:06.050 align:middle line:90%
But it was really a gift.

00:24:06.050 --> 00:24:09.470 align:middle line:84%
Because when I look
back, that relationship

00:24:09.470 --> 00:24:13.250 align:middle line:84%
afforded me the
ability and the space

00:24:13.250 --> 00:24:16.230 align:middle line:90%
to do really deep inner work.

00:24:16.230 --> 00:24:21.760 align:middle line:84%
And even though it was
painful when I got out of it

00:24:21.760 --> 00:24:24.840 align:middle line:90%
I got to find out who am I?

00:24:24.840 --> 00:24:26.600 align:middle line:84%
How do I want to
be in the world?

00:24:26.600 --> 00:24:28.840 align:middle line:90%
How do I want to share my gifts?

00:24:28.840 --> 00:24:33.290 align:middle line:84%
You know, who am I if I'm
not in a relationship,

00:24:33.290 --> 00:24:35.000 align:middle line:90%
being what somebody else needs?

00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:37.060 align:middle line:84%
Who am I?
And that was big.

00:24:37.060 --> 00:24:38.360 align:middle line:84%
That's a big one
for women in general.

00:24:38.360 --> 00:24:40.210 align:middle line:84%
Oh.
Totally,

00:24:40.210 --> 00:24:43.700 align:middle line:84%
I think if there is a gender
divide, that is a really

00:24:43.700 --> 00:24:45.310 align:middle line:90%
big one between men and women.

00:24:45.310 --> 00:24:48.091 align:middle line:84%
Women so define themselves by
the relationships they're in.

00:24:48.091 --> 00:24:48.990 align:middle line:84%
Well.
Yeah.

00:24:48.990 --> 00:24:50.580 align:middle line:90%
We're inculturated.

00:24:50.580 --> 00:24:53.770 align:middle line:84%
I mean people are giving us
dolls and little cook things

00:24:53.770 --> 00:24:54.680 align:middle line:90%
from the time we're little.

00:24:54.680 --> 00:24:59.040 align:middle line:84%
You know it was like,
this is what you do.

00:24:59.040 --> 00:25:05.600 align:middle line:84%
But for me it was like,
wow , if I stop dating,

00:25:05.600 --> 00:25:08.720 align:middle line:84%
if I'm not looking
for Mr. Right,

00:25:08.720 --> 00:25:10.650 align:middle line:90%
then who am I and what do I do?

00:25:10.650 --> 00:25:13.500 align:middle line:90%
And it it led me back to school.

00:25:13.500 --> 00:25:16.070 align:middle line:84%
It opened up new ways
of thinking for me.

00:25:16.070 --> 00:25:18.810 align:middle line:84%
It opened up a new
career path for me.

00:25:18.810 --> 00:25:26.320 align:middle line:84%
And it really allowed me to
look at my thought patterns

00:25:26.320 --> 00:25:29.310 align:middle line:90%
and what I was creating.

00:25:29.310 --> 00:25:33.780 align:middle line:84%
And then it also helps
you understand the nature

00:25:33.780 --> 00:25:36.330 align:middle line:84%
of your connection with
friends and other people

00:25:36.330 --> 00:25:39.061 align:middle line:84%
in you're-- maybe not immediate
family-- but in the environment

00:25:39.061 --> 00:25:40.840 align:middle line:84%
around you.
That changes with it.

00:25:40.840 --> 00:25:42.510 align:middle line:84%
You're not having the
same conversations

00:25:42.510 --> 00:25:43.720 align:middle line:90%
with people anymore.

00:25:43.720 --> 00:25:44.450 align:middle line:90%
That's a big one.

00:25:44.450 --> 00:25:46.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean I've been through
that where it's, I

00:25:46.220 --> 00:25:49.260 align:middle line:84%
don't want to participate
in that level of discussion

00:25:49.260 --> 00:25:50.040 align:middle line:90%
anymore.

00:25:50.040 --> 00:25:53.411 align:middle line:84%
And friends react very
quickly to know that.

00:25:53.411 --> 00:25:54.590 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
Sometimes they leave.

00:25:54.590 --> 00:25:55.290 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:25:55.290 --> 00:25:57.840 align:middle line:84%
When you're in the pattern
of-- whatever it is together--

00:25:57.840 --> 00:25:59.510 align:middle line:84%
they're not getting
the satisfaction

00:25:59.510 --> 00:26:01.020 align:middle line:84%
from the same
relationship anymore.

00:26:01.020 --> 00:26:02.990 align:middle line:84%
It's not the same relationship.
-Right.

00:26:02.990 --> 00:26:04.430 align:middle line:84%
And you know when
the relationship

00:26:04.430 --> 00:26:07.260 align:middle line:84%
ended, when the marriage
ended, some people

00:26:07.260 --> 00:26:09.780 align:middle line:90%
just exited all together.

00:26:09.780 --> 00:26:12.281 align:middle line:84%
And I really believe that they
created space for the new tribe

00:26:12.281 --> 00:26:13.640 align:middle line:84%
to come in.
-Yes.

00:26:13.640 --> 00:26:14.339 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:26:14.339 --> 00:26:19.110 align:middle line:84%
And so I ended up at this
small spiritual community.

00:26:19.110 --> 00:26:21.230 align:middle line:84%
And at that point
Michael Bernard Beckwith

00:26:21.230 --> 00:26:23.210 align:middle line:84%
was a practitioner there.
-Oh, yes.

00:26:23.210 --> 00:26:24.230 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:26:24.230 --> 00:26:27.600 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of us kind
of migrated into this place

00:26:27.600 --> 00:26:28.550 align:middle line:90%
at the same time.

00:26:28.550 --> 00:26:30.330 align:middle line:84%
And so we went to
classes together,

00:26:30.330 --> 00:26:34.030 align:middle line:84%
we had these deep conversations,
we support each other

00:26:34.030 --> 00:26:37.240 align:middle line:84%
through health challenges,
through going to school,

00:26:37.240 --> 00:26:38.720 align:middle line:90%
through raising our children.

00:26:38.720 --> 00:26:40.370 align:middle line:90%
I mean it was powerful.

00:26:40.370 --> 00:26:42.910 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that
you had to deal with--

00:26:42.910 --> 00:26:45.360 align:middle line:84%
and you talk about at great
length, including in you're

00:26:45.360 --> 00:26:49.280 align:middle line:84%
working with other people--
is the body has its own memory

00:26:49.280 --> 00:26:50.640 align:middle line:90%
of anything we're experiencing.

00:26:50.640 --> 00:26:52.590 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't have
to be physical abuse.

00:26:52.590 --> 00:26:54.300 align:middle line:84%
But where you have
physical abuse

00:26:54.300 --> 00:26:56.710 align:middle line:90%
it may be even more pronounced.

00:26:56.710 --> 00:26:58.251 align:middle line:84%
-It's encoded.
-It's encoded.

00:26:58.251 --> 00:26:58.950 align:middle line:10%
Yeah,

00:26:58.950 --> 00:27:02.610 align:middle line:10%
What I discovered is that
in the five generations

00:27:02.610 --> 00:27:07.030 align:middle line:10%
there were distinct things that
kept showing up each generation

00:27:07.030 --> 00:27:08.590 align:middle line:10%
that were in the body.

00:27:08.590 --> 00:27:13.650 align:middle line:10%
And so the majority of
the women in my family

00:27:13.650 --> 00:27:19.160 align:middle line:10%
died with illnesses, overweight,
emotional challenges, that

00:27:19.160 --> 00:27:21.510 align:middle line:10%
showed up in very similar ways.

00:27:21.510 --> 00:27:25.500 align:middle line:84%
And so that caused
me to look at, well,

00:27:25.500 --> 00:27:31.200 align:middle line:84%
what is it that is in the
body that is transmitting

00:27:31.200 --> 00:27:34.430 align:middle line:84%
information and has
created neural paths

00:27:34.430 --> 00:27:36.010 align:middle line:90%
that don't support me?

00:27:36.010 --> 00:27:37.670 align:middle line:84%
And so I started doing
a lot of research

00:27:37.670 --> 00:27:41.250 align:middle line:84%
and a lot of working on my
body to open up energies.

00:27:41.250 --> 00:27:46.550 align:middle line:84%
I hired a trainer
whose expertise

00:27:46.550 --> 00:27:48.120 align:middle line:90%
was emotional challenges.

00:27:48.120 --> 00:27:51.520 align:middle line:84%
And so the person what
would-- as I was working out--

00:27:51.520 --> 00:27:53.931 align:middle line:84%
would be witnessing parts of
the body that were constricting

00:27:53.931 --> 00:27:55.890 align:middle line:84%
and stuff.
And we'd go into those places.

00:27:55.890 --> 00:27:58.840 align:middle line:84%
And I remember one time
laying on the bench

00:27:58.840 --> 00:28:01.670 align:middle line:84%
and I'm lifting the weights,
and all of a sudden I

00:28:01.670 --> 00:28:05.380 align:middle line:84%
literally felt my
stepfather on top of me.

00:28:05.380 --> 00:28:09.174 align:middle line:84%
And he said, do
not run from that.

00:28:09.174 --> 00:28:09.940 align:middle line:90%
The trainer said that?

00:28:09.940 --> 00:28:12.060 align:middle line:84%
The trainer said, do not run
from that-- as I'm pushing

00:28:12.060 --> 00:28:14.310 align:middle line:90%
this weight and sobbing.

00:28:14.310 --> 00:28:17.510 align:middle line:84%
And eventually there was
this release in my body.

00:28:17.510 --> 00:28:20.290 align:middle line:84%
And I went home and
I got in the shower

00:28:20.290 --> 00:28:24.740 align:middle line:84%
and as the water was hitting me
I realized I was feeling water

00:28:24.740 --> 00:28:27.290 align:middle line:90%
on my body for the first time.

00:28:27.290 --> 00:28:28.270 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:28:28.270 --> 00:28:29.470 align:middle line:90%
Very interesting.

00:28:29.470 --> 00:28:33.600 align:middle line:84%
But there was a dance
at another point?

00:28:33.600 --> 00:28:35.034 align:middle line:84%
Is it at that point
or another point?

00:28:35.034 --> 00:28:36.700 align:middle line:84%
I think it was another
point when you were working

00:28:36.700 --> 00:28:40.180 align:middle line:84%
with someone where
your stepfather came

00:28:40.180 --> 00:28:41.520 align:middle line:90%
through from the other side.

00:28:41.520 --> 00:28:42.830 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:28:42.830 --> 00:28:45.910 align:middle line:84%
It was a woman who was a
healer and a body worker.

00:28:45.910 --> 00:28:49.520 align:middle line:84%
And she was doing a massage
on me and she stopped.

00:28:49.520 --> 00:28:53.180 align:middle line:84%
And she said, someone
is coming through

00:28:53.180 --> 00:28:55.240 align:middle line:90%
and wants to speak to you.

00:28:55.240 --> 00:28:58.070 align:middle line:84%
And I immediately saw the
image of my stepfather

00:28:58.070 --> 00:28:59.230 align:middle line:90%
in the suit with the hat.

00:28:59.230 --> 00:29:02.750 align:middle line:84%
And right after I saw the
image she said, he's in a suit

00:29:02.750 --> 00:29:04.630 align:middle line:90%
and he's got a hat.

00:29:04.630 --> 00:29:05.380 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, yeah.

00:29:05.380 --> 00:29:06.910 align:middle line:84%
And she said he wants
to speak to you.

00:29:06.910 --> 00:29:10.791 align:middle line:84%
And I was flitting between
intrigue and anger.

00:29:10.791 --> 00:29:12.810 align:middle line:84%
-Right.
-That he was in my space.

00:29:12.810 --> 00:29:13.720 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:29:13.720 --> 00:29:15.720 align:middle line:90%
And so I said OK.

00:29:15.720 --> 00:29:17.070 align:middle line:90%
And this is what he said to me.

00:29:17.070 --> 00:29:21.250 align:middle line:84%
He said, you have been
dragging me around

00:29:21.250 --> 00:29:25.310 align:middle line:84%
and I need you to have the
angels cut the cord between us

00:29:25.310 --> 00:29:29.140 align:middle line:90%
so that we can both be free.

00:29:29.140 --> 00:29:32.270 align:middle line:84%
And it was-- I mean I fee
a little emotional about it

00:29:32.270 --> 00:29:35.980 align:middle line:84%
because it was so
stunningly true.

00:29:35.980 --> 00:29:38.690 align:middle line:84%
That I had been dragging
him through my whole life

00:29:38.690 --> 00:29:42.350 align:middle line:84%
with the anger, and the
judgments, and the resentments,

00:29:42.350 --> 00:29:44.170 align:middle line:90%
and the shame.

00:29:44.170 --> 00:29:47.940 align:middle line:84%
And we were still connected
because I wouldn't let it go.

00:29:47.940 --> 00:29:49.600 align:middle line:84%
And we don't stop
and think about that.

00:29:49.600 --> 00:29:52.200 align:middle line:84%
Did part of you resent the
fact that he was asking

00:29:52.200 --> 00:29:53.640 align:middle line:84%
you to do this
because you didn't

00:29:53.640 --> 00:29:55.410 align:middle line:90%
want to maybe do that for him?

00:29:55.410 --> 00:29:56.400 align:middle line:90%
Totally.

00:29:56.400 --> 00:29:57.561 align:middle line:84%
OK.
Talk about it.

00:29:57.561 --> 00:29:58.260 align:middle line:90%
Totally.

00:29:58.260 --> 00:30:00.580 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of us have
these things with the deceased,

00:30:00.580 --> 00:30:01.650 align:middle line:84%
on many levels.
-Well.

00:30:01.650 --> 00:30:02.350 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:30:02.350 --> 00:30:05.410 align:middle line:84%
I mean it was like he
didn't deserve to be free.

00:30:05.410 --> 00:30:09.380 align:middle line:84%
I mean I wanted him to be
in punishment and upset

00:30:09.380 --> 00:30:10.350 align:middle line:90%
and you know.

00:30:10.350 --> 00:30:13.530 align:middle line:84%
And yet a part of me knew that
when we passed the other side

00:30:13.530 --> 00:30:15.940 align:middle line:84%
you know we're not in
some place called Hell.

00:30:15.940 --> 00:30:19.300 align:middle line:84%
I mean you know that there's
a freedom of the soul.

00:30:19.300 --> 00:30:20.640 align:middle line:90%
But it was so striking.

00:30:20.640 --> 00:30:24.000 align:middle line:84%
Because really I felt like
once I got past the saying,

00:30:24.000 --> 00:30:26.710 align:middle line:84%
you know he doesn't
deserve this, it was like,

00:30:26.710 --> 00:30:28.750 align:middle line:84%
this is about my freedom.
-Right.

00:30:28.750 --> 00:30:32.020 align:middle line:84%
If I don't cut this cord,
if I don't let him go,

00:30:32.020 --> 00:30:34.160 align:middle line:84%
I will drag him into
every relationship,

00:30:34.160 --> 00:30:36.990 align:middle line:90%
every aspect of my life.

00:30:36.990 --> 00:30:38.520 align:middle line:84%
-Which you had been.
-Right.

00:30:38.520 --> 00:30:41.850 align:middle line:84%
So what happened
after this moment?

00:30:41.850 --> 00:30:42.910 align:middle line:90%
I made a decision.

00:30:42.910 --> 00:30:46.030 align:middle line:84%
I was doing a one woman
show about my life.

00:30:46.030 --> 00:30:49.394 align:middle line:84%
And the cutting of the cord
became the end of the play.

00:30:49.394 --> 00:30:51.910 align:middle line:90%


00:30:51.910 --> 00:30:53.420 align:middle line:84%
And I did it all
over the country.

00:30:53.420 --> 00:30:55.050 align:middle line:90%
And it was incredible.

00:30:55.050 --> 00:30:58.590 align:middle line:84%
Each time I did it the
cutting of that golden cord

00:30:58.590 --> 00:31:01.190 align:middle line:90%
was like a freeing of my body.

00:31:01.190 --> 00:31:04.390 align:middle line:84%
And people would stay in
the theater after the play

00:31:04.390 --> 00:31:06.730 align:middle line:84%
and want to have
discussions about it

00:31:06.730 --> 00:31:10.150 align:middle line:84%
because they wanted to know
how they could do that.

00:31:10.150 --> 00:31:12.860 align:middle line:84%
Because it was so hard
to let go of the anger,

00:31:12.860 --> 00:31:16.450 align:middle line:84%
and the resentment, and
the pain that had been

00:31:16.450 --> 00:31:18.650 align:middle line:90%
put upon them by these people.

00:31:18.650 --> 00:31:20.460 align:middle line:90%
Well let's talk about that.

00:31:20.460 --> 00:31:23.310 align:middle line:84%
Because people listening
right now may want to know,

00:31:23.310 --> 00:31:26.980 align:middle line:84%
how can I do that when I
am so angry at this person?

00:31:26.980 --> 00:31:28.890 align:middle line:84%
So how would you
recommend a person

00:31:28.890 --> 00:31:31.970 align:middle line:84%
begin the process
of cutting the cord

00:31:31.970 --> 00:31:33.880 align:middle line:90%
when you're still ticked off?

00:31:33.880 --> 00:31:35.170 align:middle line:90%
When you're still hurt.

00:31:35.170 --> 00:31:37.334 align:middle line:84%
It was actually the
first chapter of the book

00:31:37.334 --> 00:31:38.200 align:middle line:90%
in What Will Set You Free.

00:31:38.200 --> 00:31:41.861 align:middle line:84%
I have people write the story
in all the gory details.

00:31:41.861 --> 00:31:42.850 align:middle line:84%
Write it.
Write it.

00:31:42.850 --> 00:31:43.860 align:middle line:84%
Get it out.
Get it out.

00:31:43.860 --> 00:31:44.980 align:middle line:90%
Get it out.

00:31:44.980 --> 00:31:48.210 align:middle line:10%
And then to look
at the possibility,

00:31:48.210 --> 00:31:54.700 align:middle line:10%
what would my life be like if
this story wasn't running me?

00:31:54.700 --> 00:31:57.410 align:middle line:10%
If this wasn't how I
was identifying myself.

00:31:57.410 --> 00:32:00.060 align:middle line:10%
If this isn't how I
was looking at myself.

00:32:00.060 --> 00:32:02.190 align:middle line:10%
What would my life look like?

00:32:02.190 --> 00:32:05.460 align:middle line:10%
And that one little question
opens up with people.

00:32:05.460 --> 00:32:08.770 align:middle line:10%
Because they-- well,
I'd be happier.

00:32:08.770 --> 00:32:10.450 align:middle line:10%
I could have healthier
relationships.

00:32:10.450 --> 00:32:15.760 align:middle line:10%
I wouldn't be dominated by
all of these insecurities

00:32:15.760 --> 00:32:18.640 align:middle line:10%
and these feelings
of lack of worth.

00:32:18.640 --> 00:32:21.260 align:middle line:84%
And I would be able
to find out what

00:32:21.260 --> 00:32:23.720 align:middle line:90%
it is in me that's important.

00:32:23.720 --> 00:32:27.840 align:middle line:84%
What it is in me that makes
me essential to this planet.

00:32:27.840 --> 00:32:29.600 align:middle line:90%
And so that's the first thing.

00:32:29.600 --> 00:32:31.170 align:middle line:84%
And then the second
thing is to support

00:32:31.170 --> 00:32:33.200 align:middle line:90%
people in finding their voice.

00:32:33.200 --> 00:32:36.180 align:middle line:84%
Because most people who
have been-- whether it's

00:32:36.180 --> 00:32:40.020 align:middle line:84%
beaten, or sexually abused, or
just emotionally traumatized--

00:32:40.020 --> 00:32:42.230 align:middle line:90%
they have shut down their voice.

00:32:42.230 --> 00:32:45.090 align:middle line:84%
And one of the reasons that you
know that is that when you get

00:32:45.090 --> 00:32:47.730 align:middle line:84%
ready to have a conversation
that's uncomfortable,

00:32:47.730 --> 00:32:50.090 align:middle line:84%
you're throat chakra
will constrict.

00:32:50.090 --> 00:32:50.800 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:32:50.800 --> 00:32:51.900 align:middle line:90%
And it will hurt.

00:32:51.900 --> 00:32:53.420 align:middle line:90%
And your jaws will get tight.

00:32:53.420 --> 00:32:56.420 align:middle line:84%
And the back of your
head will constrict.

00:32:56.420 --> 00:32:59.660 align:middle line:84%
And those are all signs
that you have lost

00:32:59.660 --> 00:33:02.420 align:middle line:90%
your ability to use your voice.

00:33:02.420 --> 00:33:06.320 align:middle line:84%
And so you're essentially
saying that a person is

00:33:06.320 --> 00:33:07.820 align:middle line:90%
given this golden opportunity.

00:33:07.820 --> 00:33:11.730 align:middle line:84%
Once you can find it for
your own self-interest,

00:33:11.730 --> 00:33:14.790 align:middle line:84%
even not necessarily even
to release the other person

00:33:14.790 --> 00:33:17.150 align:middle line:84%
at this point, if
you can find it

00:33:17.150 --> 00:33:18.940 align:middle line:84%
in yourself to go
through this process

00:33:18.940 --> 00:33:21.051 align:middle line:84%
you get a chance
rewrite the script.

00:33:21.051 --> 00:33:21.750 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:33:21.750 --> 00:33:25.850 align:middle line:84%
And get rid of the shame and
the guilt, which is toxic.

00:33:25.850 --> 00:33:28.630 align:middle line:84%
To move into states of
forgiveness and choose.

00:33:28.630 --> 00:33:31.900 align:middle line:84%
Because you start to realize
that your life is about choice.

00:33:31.900 --> 00:33:33.780 align:middle line:90%
That every moment is a choice.

00:33:33.780 --> 00:33:39.090 align:middle line:84%
And that these experiences are
just energy and information

00:33:39.090 --> 00:33:40.850 align:middle line:84%
and that you don't
have to claim them.

00:33:40.850 --> 00:33:42.790 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't belong to you.

00:33:42.790 --> 00:33:45.130 align:middle line:84%
And that you can say, well
what does belong to me?

00:33:45.130 --> 00:33:46.550 align:middle line:90%
How do I want to show up?

00:33:46.550 --> 00:33:51.550 align:middle line:84%
And do I really want
to walk through my life

00:33:51.550 --> 00:33:56.590 align:middle line:84%
with this level of pain attached
to me as though it's a weight?

00:33:56.590 --> 00:33:58.526 align:middle line:84%
And do you want to label
yourself in that way?

00:33:58.526 --> 00:33:59.510 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:33:59.510 --> 00:34:02.770 align:middle line:84%
Even the words themselves
have a lot of power and import

00:34:02.770 --> 00:34:05.200 align:middle line:84%
in terms of what we
become in our adult lives

00:34:05.200 --> 00:34:06.660 align:middle line:90%
and throughout our lives.

00:34:06.660 --> 00:34:08.440 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to label
yourself in that way?

00:34:08.440 --> 00:34:10.070 align:middle line:84%
That's one thing I'm
really clear about.

00:34:10.070 --> 00:34:12.870 align:middle line:84%
When I hear people
talking about their lives

00:34:12.870 --> 00:34:15.550 align:middle line:84%
as victims of this, that,
and the other thing--

00:34:15.550 --> 00:34:17.170 align:middle line:90%
not a good place to come from.

00:34:17.170 --> 00:34:21.039 align:middle line:84%
I mean after all of this do
you believe in victim-hood?

00:34:21.039 --> 00:34:21.739 align:middle line:90%
Well.

00:34:21.739 --> 00:34:24.530 align:middle line:84%
You know what, I mean I know
it exists energetically.

00:34:24.530 --> 00:34:27.130 align:middle line:84%
But you know I talk to
people about this path

00:34:27.130 --> 00:34:29.360 align:middle line:90%
of chaos and unrest.

00:34:29.360 --> 00:34:33.560 align:middle line:84%
That an event happens and you
make a decision-- mentally,

00:34:33.560 --> 00:34:36.179 align:middle line:84%
emotionally, consciously,
unconsciously-- you

00:34:36.179 --> 00:34:37.010 align:middle line:90%
make a decision.

00:34:37.010 --> 00:34:40.170 align:middle line:84%
And then your whole
psyche starts looking

00:34:40.170 --> 00:34:42.210 align:middle line:90%
for proof that you're right.

00:34:42.210 --> 00:34:46.330 align:middle line:84%
And so it goes out and it starts
to create and recreate itself

00:34:46.330 --> 00:34:49.739 align:middle line:84%
until you can get to a place
where you understand that it's

00:34:49.739 --> 00:34:51.770 align:middle line:90%
all made up in your mind.

00:34:51.770 --> 00:34:55.050 align:middle line:84%
That you know when a lot of the
scientists talk about the fact

00:34:55.050 --> 00:34:56.850 align:middle line:84%
that they drop these
chemicals and attach

00:34:56.850 --> 00:35:02.000 align:middle line:84%
the feelings in all that, that
your mind is mastering you.

00:35:02.000 --> 00:35:04.810 align:middle line:84%
As opposed to you choosing
how you want to live.

00:35:04.810 --> 00:35:05.870 align:middle line:90%
And how you want to show up.

00:35:05.870 --> 00:35:08.590 align:middle line:84%
And how you want to
express in this world.

00:35:08.590 --> 00:35:12.430 align:middle line:84%
That you are not a victim
of anything or anyone.

00:35:12.430 --> 00:35:14.700 align:middle line:84%
You get to say how
you want to live.

00:35:14.700 --> 00:35:16.640 align:middle line:84%
And if people can't
accept it and love you

00:35:16.640 --> 00:35:19.130 align:middle line:84%
the way that you
are, authentically,

00:35:19.130 --> 00:35:20.600 align:middle line:90%
then they don't belong there.

00:35:20.600 --> 00:35:21.490 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:35:21.490 --> 00:35:24.330 align:middle line:84%
Well this obviously
leads to forgiveness,

00:35:24.330 --> 00:35:25.640 align:middle line:90%
the subject of forgiveness.

00:35:25.640 --> 00:35:28.380 align:middle line:84%
And everybody has a different
take on what that word means.

00:35:28.380 --> 00:35:30.790 align:middle line:84%
I have my own take on
what that word means

00:35:30.790 --> 00:35:32.840 align:middle line:90%
and diffusing that subject.

00:35:32.840 --> 00:35:36.870 align:middle line:84%
How do you-- how do you
view the word forgiveness?

00:35:36.870 --> 00:35:40.030 align:middle line:90%
And the actual act?

00:35:40.030 --> 00:35:43.550 align:middle line:84%
Well, you know everything is
viewed from my point of view

00:35:43.550 --> 00:35:47.640 align:middle line:84%
through perception,
through filters.

00:35:47.640 --> 00:35:50.380 align:middle line:84%
And so whenever
you've made a decision

00:35:50.380 --> 00:35:52.200 align:middle line:84%
you judge everything
through those filters.

00:35:52.200 --> 00:35:57.390 align:middle line:84%
And so forgiveness is really
forgiveness of us, of self.

00:35:57.390 --> 00:36:00.780 align:middle line:84%
Letting go of those perceptions
that do not support your health

00:36:00.780 --> 00:36:02.340 align:middle line:90%
and your well being.

00:36:02.340 --> 00:36:06.090 align:middle line:84%
And then deciding to choose
what you are calling in.

00:36:06.090 --> 00:36:06.930 align:middle line:90%
I'm choosing love.

00:36:06.930 --> 00:36:07.860 align:middle line:90%
I'm choosing peace.

00:36:07.860 --> 00:36:10.170 align:middle line:84%
And so you-- first
of all, I don't

00:36:10.170 --> 00:36:14.510 align:middle line:84%
believe that spiritually
people have to be forgiven.

00:36:14.510 --> 00:36:18.370 align:middle line:84%
I think the universe loves us
wherever we are in the process.

00:36:18.370 --> 00:36:21.930 align:middle line:84%
But I think that
forgiveness is for letting

00:36:21.930 --> 00:36:25.070 align:middle line:84%
go of any perception that you
didn't deserve to be loved,

00:36:25.070 --> 00:36:27.810 align:middle line:84%
or had, or that someone
had power over you.

00:36:27.810 --> 00:36:28.770 align:middle line:90%
And that was a big one.

00:36:28.770 --> 00:36:35.050 align:middle line:84%
Because to let go of the fact
that my stepfather controlled

00:36:35.050 --> 00:36:40.810 align:middle line:84%
my life, and that I was allowing
him to do it well into my 30s,

00:36:40.810 --> 00:36:42.620 align:middle line:90%
was eye opening.

00:36:42.620 --> 00:36:45.990 align:middle line:84%
I was like, well,
if he's not, and I

00:36:45.990 --> 00:36:49.140 align:middle line:84%
can let that go,
and step back-- I

00:36:49.140 --> 00:36:52.550 align:middle line:84%
got to see all the
places I abused myself.

00:36:52.550 --> 00:36:56.360 align:middle line:84%
Over eating, over drinking,
not taking care of myself.

00:36:56.360 --> 00:37:00.116 align:middle line:84%
And it was like, oh, so now I'm
doing to me what he did to me.

00:37:00.116 --> 00:37:01.270 align:middle line:84%
Exactly.
Yeah.

00:37:01.270 --> 00:37:03.610 align:middle line:90%
And I can choose differently.

00:37:03.610 --> 00:37:05.370 align:middle line:90%
I can choose to love me.

00:37:05.370 --> 00:37:08.190 align:middle line:84%
And in addition, there's
another component to that.

00:37:08.190 --> 00:37:11.480 align:middle line:84%
And in my perception, which
is when you start looking more

00:37:11.480 --> 00:37:14.270 align:middle line:84%
deeply at the other
person as well,

00:37:14.270 --> 00:37:17.080 align:middle line:84%
you usually start
seeing the same patterns

00:37:17.080 --> 00:37:18.440 align:middle line:90%
in their own life.

00:37:18.440 --> 00:37:22.191 align:middle line:84%
Your father was also subject
to abuse when he was young.

00:37:22.191 --> 00:37:23.590 align:middle line:84%
-Yes.
-You're stepfather.

00:37:23.590 --> 00:37:25.040 align:middle line:84%
Yeah.
Alcoholism.

00:37:25.040 --> 00:37:25.739 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:37:25.739 --> 00:37:27.190 align:middle line:84%
And the stepfather
had a lot of abuse.

00:37:27.190 --> 00:37:31.750 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is that
when I work with people

00:37:31.750 --> 00:37:34.990 align:middle line:84%
you find out that there have
been generations of this stuff

00:37:34.990 --> 00:37:37.490 align:middle line:90%
that people have carried.

00:37:37.490 --> 00:37:41.760 align:middle line:84%
But what I tell people
is, you can stop it today.

00:37:41.760 --> 00:37:44.210 align:middle line:90%
You can stop it today.

00:37:44.210 --> 00:37:47.460 align:middle line:84%
Just because it came
through five generations,

00:37:47.460 --> 00:37:48.850 align:middle line:90%
the buck can stop here.

00:37:48.850 --> 00:37:53.500 align:middle line:84%
You can shift yourself and
model for your children

00:37:53.500 --> 00:37:54.990 align:middle line:90%
what's possible.

00:37:54.990 --> 00:37:58.750 align:middle line:84%
And what I found-- and I
don't totally understand it--

00:37:58.750 --> 00:38:03.420 align:middle line:84%
but it shifted going back in
time with my family members.

00:38:03.420 --> 00:38:05.500 align:middle line:84%
An aunt who passed
away-- I mean we

00:38:05.500 --> 00:38:07.334 align:middle line:84%
had an incredible
conversation where she talked

00:38:07.334 --> 00:38:08.700 align:middle line:84%
about something that
had happened to her,

00:38:08.700 --> 00:38:11.610 align:middle line:84%
and released it for the
first time in '65 years.

00:38:11.610 --> 00:38:13.340 align:middle line:90%
My mother had shifts.

00:38:13.340 --> 00:38:16.570 align:middle line:84%
And my relatives have had
shifts because they've

00:38:16.570 --> 00:38:17.940 align:middle line:90%
seen the shifts in me.

00:38:17.940 --> 00:38:20.330 align:middle line:84%
It has an impact in
your entire environment.

00:38:20.330 --> 00:38:21.520 align:middle line:90%
The whole matrix changes.

00:38:21.520 --> 00:38:23.701 align:middle line:84%
When one person gets it,
the whole matrix changes.

00:38:23.701 --> 00:38:25.120 align:middle line:84%
-Exactly.
-Absolutely.

00:38:25.120 --> 00:38:27.720 align:middle line:84%
And that's a power-- that's
a very powerful kind of take

00:38:27.720 --> 00:38:29.220 align:middle line:90%
away in this conversation.

00:38:29.220 --> 00:38:31.130 align:middle line:90%
And for me to understand.

00:38:31.130 --> 00:38:33.240 align:middle line:84%
To simply understand
another person's journey

00:38:33.240 --> 00:38:35.630 align:middle line:84%
defuses a lot of the
personal part of it.

00:38:35.630 --> 00:38:37.490 align:middle line:90%
It's like OK, yes.

00:38:37.490 --> 00:38:39.270 align:middle line:84%
And I have not been through
what you've been through.

00:38:39.270 --> 00:38:43.330 align:middle line:84%
So I don't know how I would
feel under those circumstances.

00:38:43.330 --> 00:38:45.960 align:middle line:84%
But to the degree that one
can feel like you maybe

